---
import ConditionPage from '../../components/ConditionPage.astro';
---
<ConditionPage
	title="Treatment in Clapham"
	highlight="Children's Neurological & Developmental"
	heroSubtitle="Every child develops differently, but if movement, coordination or milestones aren't progressing as expected, the right support can make a big difference."
	breadcrumb="Children's Neurological & Developmental"
	seoTitle="Children's Neurological & Developmental Treatment in Clapham"
	seoDescription="Specialist children's neurological and developmental physiotherapy in Clapham, London. Play-based, child-friendly support for movement, balance and coordination."
	introImage="/condition/childrens-neurological-developmental/therapy-session.jpg"
	whoImage="/condition/childrens-neurological-developmental/baby-crawling.jpg"
	intro={[
		"Every child develops differently, but if movement, coordination or milestones aren't progressing as expected, the right support can make a big difference.",
		"We take a practical, child-friendly approach to help children build confidence in how they move, play and interact with the world around them.",
	]}
	symptomsHeading="When to get"
	symptomsHighlight="support"
	symptomsIntro="It's worth getting an assessment if your child is experiencing any of the following:"
	symptomsList={[
		"Delays in sitting, crawling or walking",
		"Favouring one side of the body or moving asymmetrically",
		"Frequent tripping or difficulty with balance and coordination",
		"Unusual muscle tone (very floppy or very stiff)",
		"Walking differences such as toe-walking or in-toeing",
		"Difficulty with fine motor skills like reaching or hand coordination",
	]}
	treatmentHeading="How we"
	treatmentHighlight="help"
	treatmentIntro="Your child's plan is built around their needs and may include:"
	treatmentList={[
		"Physiotherapy for movement, strength and coordination",
		"Vojta therapy or reflex locomotion therapy",
		"Play-based exercises to develop motor skills",
		"Balance and coordination training",
		"Task-based activities to improve functional skills",
		"Advice for parents on supporting development at home",
		"Strategies to build confidence in movement and play",
	]}
	whoHeading="Who we"
	whoHighlight="help"
	whoList={[
		"Children with developmental delay",
		"Children with coordination difficulties (including dyspraxia)",
		"Neurological conditions such as cerebral palsy",
		"Children with balance and movement challenges",
		"Neurodiverse children with coordination or motor skill struggles",
		"Children in rehabilitation following injury or surgery",
	]}
	faqs={[
		{ q: "What happens in the first session?", a: "We keep things relaxed and child-friendly. We'll assess movement through play and talk through your concerns and goals." },
		{ q: "Can physiotherapy help if my child is clumsy?", a: "Yes. coordination issues can often be improved with the right exercises and guidance." },
		{ q: "Is therapy play-based?", a: "Yes. Children learn best through play, so sessions are designed to feel engaging while still being structured and effective." },
		{ q: "Will we get exercises to do at home?", a: "Absolutely. We'll give you simple, practical ideas to support your child between sessions." },
		{ q: "Is it too late to start if my child is older?", a: "Not at all. Children continue to develop and adapt, and we can help at any stage." },
	]}
/>
